values:
So, it looks like another mostly-private livejournal.  I'm okay with that.  I don't mind.  Something to write in when I don't feel like writing in my book-journal.

Yeah.  I'm a strange one.

I feel like with every turn I take what I know becomes less and less. The more I think about whether I really want to be an art major and whether I can really handle it, I become more and more confused. And it's not just the art major, it's college, it's Brevard, it's my life. I don't know what I'm going to do after college. And I don't know if I will even be in college after this semester. I can't imagine myself signing up for autumn classes, and I can't imagine myself transferring somewhere else, and I can't see myself getting a job and moving on. All I can imagine is the past and things happening differently than they did.

My faith is bobbing back and forth, too. I want to choose Jesus over this earthly life, I want to choose being in love with the Lord over being cool and liked and witty and beautiful. I want to choose to rely on Him alone over the option of relying on something else that's never let me down. I want this fire, this passion in my search and I want to feel like nothing else matters but the fact that I am His daughter.

Really, I want things to be clearer than they are right now. Jesus, give me peace and strength and love and motivation.

um

i never update

sorry

i forget about livejournal

i don't know anyone on here

i use xanga and myspace too much to remember

and then there's facebook and flickr

maybe i'll update more later in life

jesus is love

a blinded moment
and one more time i die
a losing battle long-forgotten still raging deep inside
all control is lost as
knot by hastened knot
demons breaking free of sloppy binds
come overloading circuits in the mind
no thinking before speaking or looking before leaping
darkened tears already leaking
on so many
different levels
am
i
speaking

So I figured I needed to update since I had started this silly little livejournal thing.  (Killing time while my photos upload...)  But I don't really feel like talking about my life right now, so I am being lazy and posting an old something that I wrote.  It isn't polished, just raw me some months ago, but it's something to fill up space so that's what I'm doing.  I guess it's called "here we go again."



confidence in self
she's low in supply and knows
too many options not enough know how
here we go again
when i'm up i'm up
when i'm down i'm down
caught up in life
barely getting left behind
don't know what yesterday felt like
one more time let's circle around
over and over hit the ground
high flying risk she's safe and sound
that's what she thinks now
tomorrow is another day
another thought another way to fall
here we go again



I would also like to say that I have changed a lot over the past year.  And by a lot I mean intensely-upside-down-run-around-the-world-twelve-times-in-two-seconds.  The Lord is mysterious and grand and awe-inspiring.  That is all.
